  "description": [
    "EDITORIAL PAGE OF THE Citizens Associations The Voice of Washington The citizens associations of Washington representing prob ably the largest organized group of our citizenry are starting their fall meetings at a time when many problems demand the attention and consideration of the general public The present Administration and the coming session of Con gress are being called upon to deal with many matters which have a direct and important bearing upon the welfare of all of our people The Administration and the Congress can receive the views and opinions of the voteless people of Washington only through the actions of the citizens associations and the other trade and civic groups of the city It has long been recognized on Capitol Hill and at the White House that the citizens associations represent the great bulk of our people Likewise it has long been recognized on Capitol Hill that a larger membership in these associations and a more active participation in their deliberations by all residents of the city would materially assist Congress in determining the local Viewpoint The coming session of Congress will have to deal with many local problems and the citizens associations will perform an important public service"
